file.name: meta.yaml
file.content:
# Meta properties that covers the breadth of the openapi spec
#   with minimal component and paths, no responses or parameters

openapi: 3.0.0

info:
  title: Meta API Test
  description: Random APIs that don't make any sense apart from testing
  version: 1.0.0
  contact:
    name: some name
    url: https://example.com
    email: abcd@example.com
  license:
    name: license name
    url: https://example.com/license

servers:
  - url: https://example.com/dev
    description: dev
  - url: https://example/com/sit
    description: sit

paths:
  /endpoint-1:
    get:
      summary: Get Endpoint
      description: |
        Here's a description filler
      operationId: "GET_ENDPOINT_1"
      tags: ["Test"]

      responses:
        "200":
          description: OK
          headers:
            content-type:
              $ref: "#/components/headers/content-type"

components:
  headers:
    content-type:
      schema:
        type: string
        example: application/json
  securitySchemes:
    BearerJWT:
      description: |
        Bearer token JWT
      type: http
      scheme: bearer
      bearerFormat: "eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJhdXRoSW........."

tags:
  - name: "Test"
    description: "Test OpenAPI YAML"

security:
  - BearerJWT: []

externalDocs:
  description: Some example docs
  url: https://example.com/external-docs
